production-retail-analytics-db

Day 10 Week 2 portfolio project.

## Problem Statement:
A retail company needs a reliable postgrsql database for string orders and an analaytics
model for reporting on sales performence

## Objective:
Design a production style database with constraints , sample data, an analytics star schema 
, and business reportings queries

## Tech stack
Postgresql
SQL
Data modeling
star schema design

# The OLTP Design
The OLTP schema stores operationals data such as customers , products, orders, order items , store , payment

## The OLAP Design
The OLAP schema uses a star schema with fact_sales at the centee and dimension tables for customers
products, stores and dates

# Data quality rules
Customers must have unique emails
product prices cannot be negative
qunatities must be greater than zero
orders must use valid statuses
payment must belong to valid orders

## Business questions answered

what is monthly revenue?
which product categories generates the most revnue?
who are the top customers?
which stores perform best?
which products sell the most?
which products sell the most?

